Separate environment for Kali to negate conflicts

Update package list
sudo apt-get update

Install Python and pip:
sudo apt-get install python3 python3-pip

Install Node.js and npm:
sudo apt-get install nodejs npm

Create a virtual environment (optional but recommended):
sudo apt-get install python3-venv
python3 -m venv myenv
source myenv/bin/activate

Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt


Install JavaScript Analysis Tools
npm install -g jshint eslint


Create Project Directory Structure and Files:
mkdir -p code_review_tool/analyzers code_review_tool/config code_review_tool/reports code_review_tool/utils code_review_tool/tests
touch code_review_tool/analyzers/__init__.py code_review_tool/config/__init__.py code_review_tool/reports/__init__.py code_review_tool/utils/__init__.py code_review_tool/tests/__init__.py
touch code_review_tool/analyzers/base_analyzer.py code_review_tool/analyzers/python_analyzer.py code_review_tool/analyzers/javascript_analyzer.py
touch code_review_tool/config/config.py code_review_tool/reports/report_generator.py code_review_tool/utils/logger.py code_review_tool/utils/error_handler.py
touch code_review_tool/main.py code_review_tool/config/config.json
